Policy.acknowledgement_statement: The dataset used for the analyses described in this manuscript were obtained for the database of Genotype and Phenotype (dbGaP) found at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gap [accession number phs000714.v1.p1]. Samples and associated were provided by the NICHD-funded Genomic and Proteomic Network for Preterm Birth Research (GPN-PBR). The contents of this reportrepresent the views of the authors and do not necessarily represent the the views of the NICHD or the GPN-PBR.
Policy.ic_specific_access_term:
Former members of the NICHD Genomic and Proteomic Network for Preterm Birth Research (GPN-PBR) are exempt from the embargo date and can publish freely.
The progress report should should specifically cite work done that relates to this dataset [NICHD Genomic and Proteomic Network for Preterm Birth Research] and not just a generic report for a series of datasets that may have been requested.

GSR_Access.gsr_mode_label: Unrestricted access (institution responded that the study is not sensitive without submitting a new Institutional Certification)

ConsentGroup.title: Disease-Specific (Pregnancy Complications, RD)
ConsentGroup.name: DS-PREG-COM-RD
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction:
Use of the data must be related to Pregnancy Complications and related disorders.
Use of data is limited to genetic and biomedical research on pregnancy complications, such as preterm birth, preeclampsia, fetal growth restriction, etc. and their consequences on the neonate. Data cannot be used to determine the individual identity of any study participant or their relationship to another person.
